<TITLE> AL leader expelled over girl caning </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Brahmanbaria, May 25 (bdnews24.com)The ruling Awami league's Bancharampur upazila unit has expelled one of its leaders for his alleged involvement in issuing a fatwa to cane a young girl. Golam Zilani, AL chairman of Faridabad union in Brahmanbaria district, was temporarily suspended on charges of presiding over a village arbitration that decided to lash the girl 101 times. Bancharampur upazila AL chairman told reporters that an emergency meeting of the unit decided to suspend Zilani, who is also the upazila's elected chairman. A Bengali-language daily published a report on May 22 that four people were arrested after the girl was lashed on May 19. The High Court on Monday asked the government to explain why extra-judicial punishment in the name of fatwa and Islami Sharia law would not be declared illegal and inhuman. The court rule came upon a petition filed by two lawyers b
